    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Miklós Oláh (Augsburg, 9 March 1551)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>Gergely Bornemissza, George Martinuzzi’s legate, has handed over Oláh’s
                            letter. Bornemissza has come to Augsburg and presented what had been
                            entrusted to him. Since King Ferdinand I wants to be in Vienna within
                            eight days, he has postponed the legate’s matter until then to think
                            about the answer. He will let Oláh know so Oláh can be there when he
                            arrives.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Ferdinandus etc. Reverendissime Fidelis nobis Dilecte! </p>
                <p>Reddidit nobis litteras<note type="critic">We do not know this
                        letter.</note> Devotionis Tuae <persName>Gregorius
                        Bornemissa</persName><note type="critic">Gergely Bornemissza.</note> nuntius
                    reverendissimi <persName>episcopi Waradiensis</persName>,<note type="critic"
                        >George Martinuzzi.</note> qui hodie huc
                        <placeName>Augustam</placeName><note type="critic">Augsburg.</note>
                    applicuit, nosque <del corresp="scriba">tamen</del><add corresp="scriba"
                        type="corr">primum</add> a meridie inter secundam et tertiam horam convenit
                    et mandata sua nobis exposuit. Cum utro <del corresp="scriba"> cras
                        discessivi</del> cras discedere et intra octiduum
                        <placeName>Viennam</placeName> dante Deo pervenire statuerimus, eiusdem
                    nuntii expeditionem eo usque differendam esse censuimus, ut illis omnibus <del
                        corresp="scriba">maturius deliberare</del> ponderitis <del corresp="scriba"
                        >eo</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">tanto</add> melius respondere, et
                    deinde ipsum nuntium, quem <del corresp="scriba">eo etiamsi</del> pro nunc eo
                    remisimus, recta ad ipsum <persName>Waradiensem</persName><note type="critic"
                        >Martinuzzi was also Bishop of Oradea.</note>
                    <del corresp="scriba">ac remittere</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr"
                        >expedire</add> possimus. Quod <del corresp="scriba">tibi</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">Devotioni Tuae</add> ideo significamus, ut in
                    adventu istic nostro <del corresp="scriba">nobis tu</del> Devotio Tua quoque ibi
                    adsit. </p>
                <p>Datum <placeName>Augustae</placeName> die 9. Martii 1551.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>Probably on the outer side:</head>
                <p>Agriensi.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
